+        <h1>Rullst Admin Panel</h1>
+<p>Rullst ORM includes a completely free, drop-in web dashboard that automatically reads your <code>#[derive(Orm)]</code> models and lets you manage your database graphically. </p>
+<p>Unlike traditional ORMs that charge for their studio/admin tools, Rullst provides this natively.</p>
+<h2>How it Works</h2>
+<p>The Admin Panel is simply a gorgeous HTML/CSS/JS frontend generated by the ORM itself. It relies on standard REST endpoints that you expose via your favorite web framework.</p>
+<h3>Example using Axum</h3>
+<p>To serve the dashboard, you just map the <code>dashboard_html()</code> function to a route:</p>
+<pre><code class="language-rust">use axum::{routing::get, Router, response::Html};
+use rullst_orm::dashboard_html;
+
+#[tokio::main]
+async fn main() {
+    let app = Router::new()
+        .route(&quot;/admin&quot;, get(|| async { Html(dashboard_html()) }));
+
+    let listener = tokio::net::TcpListener::bind(&quot;127.0.0.1:3000&quot;).await.unwrap();
+    println!(&quot;Admin Panel available at http://localhost:3000/admin&quot;);
+
+    axum::serve(listener, app).await.unwrap();
+}
+</code></pre>
+<h2>Features</h2>
+<ul>
+<li><strong>Dark Mode Native</strong>: A stunning, premium dark interface out-of-the-box.</li>
+<li><strong>Audit Logs View</strong>: Directly inspect <code>rullst_audits</code> to see revision history.</li>
+<li><strong>Zero Config</strong>: No React/Vue compilation required. Just serve the string!</li>
+</ul>
+
+    </main>
